BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: LA CLINICA DE LOS CAMPESINOS INC

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ENSURE ACCESS TO HIGH QUALITY INTEGRATED HEALTHCARE AND PROMOTE THE WELL-BEING OF OUR PATIENTS, STAFF, AND COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO ENSURE ACCESS TO HIGH QUALITY INTEGRATED HEALTHCARE AND PROMOTE THE WELL-BEING OF OUR PATIENTS, STAFF, AND COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.Desc: COMMUNITY AND MIGRANT HEALTH CLINIC CENTER THAT PROVIDES PRIMARY MEDICAL, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH, AND DENTAL HEALTH SERVICES TO COMMUNITY RESIDENTS AND MIGRANT PATIENTS. THE WISCONSIN COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER GRANT ENABLES LA CLINICA TO PROVIDE COMMUNITY AND MIGRANT PATIENTS ACCESS TO MEDICAL AND DENTAL SERVICES. IN ADDITION, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES ARE PROVIDED WHICH INCLUDE MEDICATION ASSISTED TREATMENT FOR SUBSTANCE AND ALCOHOL ABUSE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE WOMEN, INFANT, AND CHILDREN'S GRANT ALLOWS LA CLINICA TO PROVIDE SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION AND EDUCATION TO CLIENTS IN THE PROGRAM SERVICES AREA.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: LA CLINICA DE LOS CAMPESINOS IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION THAT PROVIDES HEALTHCARE SERVICES THROUGH MEDICAL, BEHAVIORAL AND DENTAL CLINICS. IT IS NOT REQUIRED TO BE LICENSED AS A HOSPITAL AND THEREFORE IS NOT REQUIRED TO COMPLETE SCHEDULE H.

OtherLiabilitiesOrgGrp.Desc: RIGHT OF USE OBLIGATION - OPERATING LEASE

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TO ACCOUNT FOR ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS, THE CLINIC DETERMINES WHETHER IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT A TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY THE TAXING AUTHORITIES BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION, ASSUMING THE TAXING AUTHORITY HAS FULL KNOWLEDGE OF ALL INFORMATION. IF THE TAX POSITION DOES NOT MEET THE MORE LIKELY-THAN-NOT RECOGNITION THRESHOLD, THE BENEFIT OF THE TAX POSITION IS NOT RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT DOES NOT BELIEVE THE CLINIC HAS ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS OR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS.
THE SCHOLARSHIPS AWARDED ARE MANAGED BY AN OUTSIDE FOUNDATION. THE FOUNDATION MAINTAINS THE RECORDS AND ENSURES THE RECIPIENTS MEET THE ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PREPARED FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE CFO AND CEO AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNUALLY ALL DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS DISCLOSE ALL INFORMATION REGARDING THEIR INTERESTS AND THOSE OF THEIR FAMILY MEMBERS THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS THE MEMBERS OF GOVERNING BODY MAKE DETERMINATIONS OF WHETHER A CONFLICT EXISTS AND REVIEW ACTUAL CONFLICTS. ANY PERSON WITH A CONFLICT IS PROHIBITED FROM PARTICIPATING IN THE GOVERNING BODY'S DELIBERATIONS AND DECISIONS IN THE TRANSACTION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ANNUALLY DETERMINE THE CEO'S COMPENSATION USING DATA ON COMPENSATION PAID BY COMPARABLE ORGANIZATIONS IN SIMILAR COMMUNITIES FOR SIMILAR SERVICES

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
